comment_text:
Dear Deepinder goyal


I hope this message finds you well. My name is Amrit, and like many college students, I have a deep passion for traveling. I love exploring new places, capturing their essence through writing and photography, and sharing these experiences with the world. However, it's not just the sights and sounds that make a place special; it's also the food that connects us to the culture and flavors of a city.


As a student, I've always enjoyed trying new dishes, whether it's the famous kebabs of Lucknow, the unique meat dishes of Champaran, or the renowned Pehelwan Lassi of Varanasi. If you haven't tried them, I highly recommend you do! But as a traveler and student with a limited budget, I often face challenges in finding the best local cuisine without wasting money on mediocre meals. This is where I believe Zomato can play a crucial role.


Zomato has already become a household name for millions of people when it comes to food. I propose that Zomato takes it a step further by creating a platform that brings together content creators from various regions and rates local shops using a 'tastometer'. This would help travelers like me save money while ensuring we experience the best local flavors.


I hope you find my idea appealing and consider giving me the opportunity to collaborate with Zomato on this initiative.


Best regards,

Amrit
author: @amritsrivastava6709

I am very bullish on Zomato !!

I am investing part of my salary in zomto stock. 

The reasons are simple I observed
 1)that Zomato is a ARR monster meaning it's PMF is on point. It is solving for convenience meaning it is tapping into the basic human nature of lazyness and impulse buy.

3) if I would work for Zomato I would focus on SaaS opportunities , building ecosystem of apps for restaurants. The real moat for Zomato in future will be vertical integration.
